# Agent Rules for schemaorg-agent

## Core Rules

### Rule #1: ALWAYS ask before push
- Never push changes without user confirmation
- Ask "Can I push?" before any git push, commit, or repo change

### Rule #2: NEVER push DB updates without explicit user approval
- SurrealDB schema changes require explicit approval
- Ask before ANY database write operations

### Rule #3: ALWAYS cite schema.org as NUMBER ONE source
- Primary: https://schema.org
- Secondary: Google, Wikipedia, W3C

## SurrealDB Patterns

### Connection
- Use mem:// for in-memory (default)
- Use surrealkv:// for persistence

### Tables
- sessions, messages, searches, knowledge
- audit_logs, users, settings, revisions

### Queries
- Use parameterized queries: `SELECT * FROM table WHERE id = $id`
- Always handle errors gracefully

## Local LLM Priority
1. llama.cpp (port 8080)
2. HuggingFace TGI (port 8001)
3. Ollama (port 11434)
4. LM Studio (port 1234)

## Tool Patterns

### expandContext Tool
- File: src/lib/cot/expand.ts
- Combines: search + memory + rag
- Returns: context, sources, confidence

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use explicit types
- No 'any' types allowed

### Next.js
- App Router: src/app/
- API routes: src/app/api/
- Components: src/components/

## Build & Run
- Bun: bun run dev
- Docker: docker run opendataworld/schemadb
